-- Sino-Forest Said to Market $600 Million of Seven-Year Bonds; Pricing Today
-- B y   S h e l l e y   S m i t h
-- 2010-10-14T03:15:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-14/sino-forest-said-to-market-600-million-of-seven-year-bonds-pricing-today.html
 Sino-Forest Corp., the Mississagua,
Ontario-based forestry company that operates in China, is
marketing its sale of $600 million of seven-year bonds,
according to a person familiar with the matter.  Sino-Forest is offering the notes to investors to yield
between 6.25 percent and 6.375 percent, said the person, who
asked not to be identified because the details are private. Bank
of America Corp. and Credit Suisse Group AG are managing the
sale of notes, which are expected to price today, the person
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shelley Smith in Hong Kong at 
